We will use the formula from step 4 to compute the profit of the investor. This is computed as follows: 


$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Profit}
&={{(}}\dfrac{\text{1,000}}{\text{2 }}{\text{$\times$ \$9.00)}}{\text{ + (1,000 $\times$ \$4.00)}}\\[10pt]
&={\textbf{\$8,500.00}}
\end{aligned}$$ 


**The investor will have a profit amounting to $8,500.00**
